  <summary>The multi-system Chiptune Tracker</summary>
  <description>
    <p>DefleMask is a cross-platform chiptune music tracker.</p>
    <p>You can produce video game music for many soundchips and old school game-consoles and computers.</p>
    <p>
      <em>If it is made with DefleMask, it IS Chiptune. ;)</em>
    </p>
    <p>Supported soundchips so far:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>YAMAHA YM2612 (with Special CH3 mode)</li>
      <li>Texas Instruments SN76489 PSG</li>
      <li>Z80 Game Boy</li>
      <li>Hudson Soft HuC6280</li>
      <li>Ricoh 2A03</li>
      <li>MOS Technology SID</li>
      <li>YAMAHA YM2151</li>
      <li>SEGA PCM</li>
    </ul>
    <p>So you can make music for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>SEGA Genesis/Mega Drive</li>
      <li>SEGA Master System</li>
      <li>Nintendo Game Boy</li>
      <li>NEC PC-Engine/TurboGrafx-16</li>
      <li>Nintendo NES</li>
      <li>Commodore 64</li>
      <li>Arcade System (SEGA X/Y boards)</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
